comment: Only graded on 4 assignments (30% Midterm, 30% Final, 20% Reading Quizzes, 20% Group Project). Extremely dry, boring content, kind of assumes everyone has an advanced level of knowledge even though there are no pre reqs to the class. Exams are unnecessarily difficult - both the midterm and final had to be curved by 20 points each.

Final grade is only based on two exams, reading quizzes, and a group project. The class is pretty difficult, he had to curve the midterm and final for a decent amount of points, think 10-20. The lectures can be boring but he does a decent job teaching, willing to answer questions, and is overall a pretty chill professor.
Class was super easy. One reading quiz a week which was common sense if you read the book. Curves the midterm and final a LOT. Highly recommend for a GE and he was super nice.

Lecture could be dry at times, but I still liked this class. Just a midterm and final (both administered online), final paper, and pop tophat quizzes based on the readings. He has students best interests at heart and everything was pretty straightforward.

was an excellent lecturer. Insightful, even handed, and willing to answer questions and have a discussion. The class was based mostly on the midterms, final and paper, but he gave a generous curve and graded fairly. I really enjoyed this class.

This class is unnecessarily tedious and difficult. Endless amount of policies to choose from to study, and this prof seemingly picks the most boring topics possible. Doesn't give clear guidelines or content of exams, the quizzes don't even match the readings, and was pretentious with occasional out of pocket things said. -900/10, don't recommend.

This class was pretty easy, if you took high school gov you're off to a good start. I really liked Prof , and though I probably could've gotten an A while skipping some lectures, I genuinely enjoyed being there. Classes kind of feel like a casual chat but he does teach the material well. Funny, chill, will lightly make fun of people.

Many questions are completely ambiguous or have conflicting information which makes the midterm luck-based. Everyone ran out of time, average was initially an 80%. Now it's a 78%, and we're confused whether he curved it down? No lecture recs, mandatory attendance, midterms open at 9AM for 1 hour, & no slides released until weeks after his lectures.

Professor  is a really great professor. He is clear about what his expectations are for your assignments. There are 2 midterms, 1 final. Lots of extra credit opportunity and he also curves almost all the exams. He is very smart and yet is easy to learn from as he explains things flawlessly. He is also funny and really nice!

Aces clearly loves the information he is teaching, the class had only three test- which he curved and extra credit was able to be given. There was a textbook- but I never bought it. I put this class on the back burner of 18 credit hours- not that it is easy, just never any commitment besides the three exams.

Your grade is determined based on the final and midterm exams. The exams are extremely hard he had to curve grades 12% because a lot of our class failed. Lectures are really boring. Wouldnt recommend this course or teacher. This intro class definitely hurt my gpa. Take with another professor if you can!

The only grade in the class is the midterm and final, which isn't an easy exam, but he does curve it! I would take it with someone else if possible, but have learned a lot. It is an intro level course, but is much harder than that. Other students in my class do not like him, but I do not mind him.

The only grade in the class is the midterm and final, which isn't an easy exam, but he does curve it! I would take it with someone else if possible, but have learned a lot. It is an intro level course, but is much harder than that.

He's a great guy who loves this topic, but you don't actually get through much content in the class because he talks about it all a little too much. Graded by three response papers, two exams, one final paper, and some reading quizzes. You really need to do the reading and it's very unclear exactly what he expects you to do in the papers.

She obviously knows what she is talking about in regards to the class. However, students did not know that much, and she was not super clear in what was expected. Multiple times I got points taken off for things I would have done if I would have been told to do so. Also, attendance "wasn't mandatory", but she did random attendance checks.

She's clear as mud when it comes to everything--almost as if she is writing her dissertation on academic vagueness. Lectures are not mandatory but she throws in all sorts of attendance checks and participation activities, so you better attend. I was excited for the group project but I was stuck doing all of the work and it really dragged on.

Very unreasonable and harsh with grading group work. She would basically laugh us off when we went to her for help/clarification. She's absolutely brilliant and dedicated to her studies but I don't think she understood that her students aren't at the same level of knowledge as she is. She's moving to DC so luckily you probably won't have her.
She gives every opportunity to do well in this class and to communicate with her as an instructor. Highly recommend!

My favorite professor to learn from in 6 years at OSU. The lectures are so clear, so well thought out. The organization of the courses is fantastic. It does involve a good amount of work, but I never felt it was a waste of time or busy work. She makes me regret not choosing epidemiology or biostats as my focus for grad school.

My favorite professor to learn from in 6 years at Ohio State (undergrad + grad school). Her lectures are so clear, her organization is unbeatable, and I genuinely came away from this class feeling confident in everything she taught me. Makes me regret not doing epidemiology. There is a lot of work with the course, but nothing you don't learn from.

My experience with Dr. was very positive. I really appreciate how she teaches (you do a weekly lab and quizzes and assignments ) so you get plenty of practice before exams. She will also take time to explain concepts and make sure that you understand it by the end of her explanation. I would highly recommend taking any course with her.

Dr.  is a very difficult professor to work with and does not respect her students. When difficult situations arise in the classroom she's been shown to handle them extremely unfairly and without respect and careful consideration. If you're looking for fair treatment and respect from your professor I would not recommend Dr. .
She is a great professor; gives extremely good feedback. If you work for it, you can easily get an A
Dr.  is the Best. Recommend his American Presidency class!

Dr.  is extremely considerate and thorough. You know exactly what is going to happen and when it will happen. I knew when I signed up for his class that I would need to miss some days of class and he was very helpful in allowing me to make up missed work and assignments prior to leaving. Anything on tests/quizzes are discussed in class.

I liked taking his class but I have to say it's quite repetitive. Yeah you learn a lot but it's super boring sometimes. You can easily pass the class with an A by just using sparknotes and not reading the 2 hours of homework he wants you to do by the next lecture. But he is very knowledgeable and friendly I liked him overall just kinda boring.

LOVE LOVE LOVED this class. Dr.  has the ability to show his students how politics really works, and he does it with absolutely no bias. I took this class thinking that I knew how our government works, and I left the class with a genuine understanding of it. I recommend this class to EVERYONE at OSU Lima, whether it is a requirement or not.
Very knowledgable and helpful. His class requires a lot of reading but it is not hard material.
great instruction

I took his honors poli sci class and it was great. He is very very interested in teaching and def knows what he is talking about. group work helps a lot with class discussion and he hands everything back with a lot of feed back. a great teacher with a lot of experiance, including his own politics book that we worked with in class, def. take him!
Really knows his stuff and interested in teaching. Don't take his class early in the day though, his voice will put you to sleep fast.

Great professor, Dr.  is very helpful outside of class. His lectures are very clear, and we did a lot of group work also. The group work really helped with the lectures. Make sure you read the books, because they will help you, especially on the exams. I would highly suggest taking him, he is a great professor, and the class was really good.

I actually took this class a couple years ago, but never did this.  is a great prof and a good lecturer. Hes very passionate about the subject and that rubs off on his students. Definitely recommend this class for your GEC requirements.
No Comments
No Comments
interesting - but monotonic...
Genuinely interested in teaching. A lot of class discussion; really made the class more about the students and less about himself.

Dr.  is very kind and makes an effort to get to know all of the students. She's very interested in helping students, and the class is easy enough if you do all the assignments. There are online lectures weekly that are used for the quizzes, and a final poster project that builds throughout the semester. I would recommend taking Dr. .

Dr.  was a very good professor. I really had no interest in judgement and decision making before I entered his classroom but now I have a new understanding and respect for the subject matter. The only complaints that I would have would be we did not have a textbook which made things hard. The class is clenging but very interesting.
Very respectful of everyone's questions and comments, makes the topic very interesting. I thought the class would be dull but it actually changed my life! I strongly recommend it.
This is a very interesting class. I definitely learned a lot, but this is also a difficult class. It takes a lot of work, but it's well worth it.
Simply awesome - best professor I ever had.
He's a GREAT teacher, but watch out for the paper at the end of the class. I had to take a LOT of time to research for it. He's a great teacher and it's a great class but don't get lazy!
is a great guy, he went out of his way to help me find an article that I needed for my research paper.
Definitely keeps the lectures interesting. The readings correlate well with the lectures. I thoroughly enjoyed this class and thought he was really nice.
No Comments

Very good teacher! My favorite psych class I've taken for the past 4 years. The only hard part is that there is a big paper at the end and a cumulative final, but there are many small assigments along the way for the paper so you can't get behind.
He does know his stuff but do not get on his bad side. If you do he will undermine you in a passive aggressive way.

Course material is difficult, but he makes it understandable and interesting. Very helpful. Liberal grader and very fair. Big paper, but you pick the topic. Definitely would take him again...brilliant.
Show up, pay attention, the lectures are in depth but you will learn so much from him. When working on the paper, go to him he will you the feedback you need to pass. He is a great teacher.

is really one of the best at OSU. His tests are tough but fair, the paper is easy if you follow his instructions and go to him for help, and the reading isn't really necessary. The guy is absolutely brilliant and knows an unbelievable amount about OH politics, you will learn a ton!

Having your Ohio Politics class taught by Presdident Gee's Senior Political Advisor is pretty darn awesome! Definitely attend lectures, as  has plenty of insightful stories and experience on the subject matter. A TON of reading, but most was relevant and helpful on exams. Attendance, studying and reading are all necessary for an A!

Prof  is a very good lecturer. The class is a typical poli sci class, with two midterms that are essay based. Recitation is used to explore interesting topics. Also, there is a requirement to volunteer for a campaign 6-10 hours a week, with a paper due at the end of the quarter. Would definitely recommend prof .

Excellent. His lectures are very interesting, and he is really laid-back. You have to work for six hours per week with a campaign of your choice and write an essay about it. Do not buy the textbooks; you will never even look at them.
I thought Dr. 's Ohio Politics class was outstanding. He's the best professor I've had at the university thusfar. And no, it's not impossible to get an A in his class.

Great Prof!! Very entertaining, and very personable. He's biased, and doesn't try to hide it, but will like you no matter your opinions as long as you share your opinions. We barely used the textbooks, and the exams weren't bad if you paid attention in class. I learned a lot in this class!

Independents and third-party supporters beware: this guy often confuses facts with opinions, whether or not his students realize it. He is quite biased against certain candidates and parties, yet some of the things he says contradict with his own biased statements-- apparently not enough to get him to change his mind.. What a letdown.

LOVED his class. Learned so much! He made it interesting by actually "talking" to the class and not lecturing in a monotone class. He has a sense of humor about things,but if ur not a "favorite" don't expect to be called on. My favorite PS class ever.
Dr.  is a wonderful professor. No political science degree is complete without taking his classes. Lectures were interesting, and I learned a great deal from him.
Great lectures, you will learn a good deal about Ohio Politics.
Good prof... easy class didn't buy the books and go an A. Just show up and you'll be fine.

Great class. If you are actually a PoliSci major this is a great class and you will learn a lot. This is a high level class so no, he is not going to hold your hand and give you outlines and essay questions but it is stupid to presume that an instructor should do so. It's called college, not high school. Overall, a good class with lots of info.
Really, great guy, great class. Those claiming he is biased are absolutely ridiculous, you can be conservative as you want and the guy is respectful. Easy, fun, and informative. Take him if you can.

is the best professor at OSU! His lectures are interesting, informative, and full of relevant anecdotes. He loves what he teaches and he cares for his students. If you get to know him, he will make a great mentor and will take the time to meet with you and offer advice to you. I always looked forward to going to his classes!

decent professor and a funny guy, although you don't really learn a lot in his class. exams are not fun at all, since he doesn't provide an outline of terms or anything to that extent in the way of preperation. overall it's not that difficult of a class, just be prepared to spend time working outside of class doing volunteering, surveys, etc.
Do not even bother unless you are a democrat. Very Very liberal. Biggest name dropper in the world. Who the hell cares who Vern Riffe is, I sure don't. HAVE FUN!!!!

Excellent professor! If you want to learn about Ohio and her politics, there is no better professor to have than  ; itâ€™s definitely a class that you don't want to miss! His lectures are always informative, relevant and never boring. On a separate note, I read one of his books for another class (Polling and the Public: What Every Citize
Straight forward class: midterm, final, and paper
Good lectures. Go to class in order to do well on the tests. Grades papers slightly hard. Knows his Ohio policitcs quite well.

Prof.  is the most grounded and personable professor I've ever had. I have ADHD and I can confidently say that his lectures are amazingly engaging, I've never been bored in his class. He exudes so much passion through his lectures that it's frankly hard to not do well in his class. Overall, one of the best learning experiences in my life.

I had Professor  twice for 2 different classes, 1101 and 3460. Both times he was very enjoyable to have. He is very knowledgeable about the material that is given and the classes were both very interesting but you need to come to class and be ready to learn. Highly recommend having him.

I loved this class with . They are so enthusiastic and have so much experience to share. There is a good amount of reading that I struggled to keep up with but it rarely impacted my ability to participate. Participating in their class is so thought-provoking and you can really get a lot out of it.  will challenge you, and it rocks!

is one of those professors I will never forget. Not only are they well educated in the topic they are lecturing on, but it is very apparent that they are passionate about it as well. Their lectures are very fast paced, but that just further illustrates that they love what they do. I would take them again in a heart beat!

Dr.  is a true asset to Ohio State. His lectures are interesting. He has a great sense of humor, enjoys teaching, and his experience outside of the classroom really helps you apply what your learning. Show up for class, make note cards of the lectures, and you'll get an A. He assigned 3 math oriented assignments and 15 half page briefs.

Dr.  is an excellent professor. He seems to genuinely enjoy teaching. His lectures are interesting. I would absolutely take him again. The tests are taken directly from the lecture notes. There is a little bit of math involved in the class but this is to be expected from a chemistry class. Understand logarithms. He's funny and cares.

Dr.  is a great guy. His soil chemistry class is a difficult class, but if you come to class everyday and engage with him during lecture you will be fine. Visit him during office hours if you ever have questions and he will help you out and ease any fear you may have.
Great guy. Very clear and easy to understand.

Professor  was amazing. If you are seriously considering law school, I definitely recommend taking one of his classes. The entire class is very lecture and exam heavy, but if you truly engage in class and with the material, you will do just fine. I learned more in this class than I learned in any other political science classes combined.

is a great guy and the best professor in this department. I have taken his two classes and I can say they will humble you. Not an easy A at all. Go for every class and write down every word he says. Highly recommend if you see law school in your future. It is very likely you will not get an A in this class. If that matters to you skip this

Great guy. Loved 4136 with him, so I took this class. Anyone with any interest in the Supreme Court should take him; you will learn so much. This class wasn't as good; I'd already learned about a lot of material in his other course. Still valuable research and writing skills. He provides copious guidelines for the paper. Do that and you'll be ok.

This is one of the most interesting classes I have ever taken. While the class is very difficult (beware if you just want a grade booster), he is really passionate about the subject and I learned a lot more about the Supreme Court. The papers are long and difficult to write (20 page final paper), but it will turn out alright if you put in the work!

If you have a chance to take a class with Dr. . Do it. He is incredibly kind and cares so much for his students. Any and all of your questions will be answered in depth and he is very accommodating. The content can be a lot but if you follow the syllabus, you'll be fine

Dr.  is a fantastic professor. The final paper is long, but you will build up to it in your other two papers. By the end of the class you will have a comprehensive understanding of the court and a paper as a reference for your writing abilities. He does his best to connect with all students. I highly suggest taking even if you are not honors.

By far one of my favorite professors at OSU. His class had challenging material, but none of the assignments or exams are extremely difficult and he is great about implementing feedback. He also gave an easy extra credit assignment. I wish I had taken more classes with him while at OSU.

My favorite class I've ever taken was the one I took with him. He doesn't take attendance (though he notices those who show up) but GO TO CLASS. He's a great lecturer and if you know your lectures and cases you'll be fine . Sit towards the front to be one of Larry's favorites. You'll just want him to like you. It'll just make you feel good.

Dr.  was incredible, a 6/5. He always assumed he explained something wrong instead of getting mad at students for not understanding, he let us be curious without letting "poli sci kids" pull us off on a tangent, and he pulled from current events to teach material. The class was tough, lecture-heavy, and lots of reading for sure, but worth it.

Dr.  is my favorite professor I have had so far at OSU. He cares so much for his students and is very passionate about the content he teaches. This class is tough but he works with you and makes sure that you learn. Although I received a B I believe I learned more in his course than any of the others I took this term.

Professor  is one of the most kind, helpful professors I have ever had. The class is comprised of just three essays. They are 5, 10, and 20 pages and the 20 page is worth 70% of your grade. It seems intimidating, but he prepares you really well to do it and you will learn a ton. No attendance, but if you miss class you're screwed for the essays

Prof.  is the best professor Ive ever had at OSU as far as what I learned in the class but the class was not easy! I loved the content, but there were only 3 exams, completely essay-based and timed. I had to rewatch lectures several times to get all the information at times. It was tough, but worth it. I feel like I know so much more now!

Professor  is a fantastic instructor but also an incredibly tough grader. Class is made up entirely of exams, so don't fail any because otherwise, you'll fail the course. He also offers little to no extra credit, so don't forget to prep for exams because they're your only source of redemption.

Dr.  is one of the most kind and caring professors I've had at OSU. He does not use lecture slides, which is an adjustment at first, but is very engaging in class. His course was no cakewalk and the material bordered on dull at times, but it wasn't bad if you pay attention and study for exams.

Dr.  is one of the best professors at OSU. Truly one of the nicest, most knowledgeable, and helpful professors I've had. Not an easy A but wont make you cry yourself to sleep. Not an overwhelming amount of work but covers a lot of material. He does not use any notes and lecture is completely oral, which is an adjustment but helped me focus.

is one of my favorite professors at OSU because he cares a lot about his students. I learned a lot in this course, and not just surface-level content but a deeper understanding of the Supreme Court. I recommend recording lectures because while they are engaging, they are long, and they are pretty much your only source of class content.

Professor 's class isn't "easy" but you will learn a lot. I truly feel lucky to have been able to take 2 classes with him. You won't meet a professor at OSU that's more knowledgeable, kind, and caring. And he's hilarious.

He does not use any kind of slides or another presentation tool in class, he talks at you for 1:20 straight. This class was also graded solely on exams, which is not something I enjoy. I found recording the lectures to be somewhat helpful, but overall was not a fan of him at all. He is also confusing, sometimes going back on what he said before.

Professor  was likely the most knowledgable and accessible professor I've had. The class was comprised of 3 papers, all research-based. However, you're given the time and resources to get it done, and he is there every step of the way to help. I wish I had another class with him because he is one of the kindest and smartest professors I've had.

might be the best professor I've had at OSU. While the class is totally lecture based, the way he presents the material is so interesting and you can tell how much he knows and loves what he does. I would suggest studying early because if you do the topic guides and know them well, you'll be fine on the exams!

Prof. 's course is largely statistical and focuses on the kinda stuff most political science students probably already know (at least in a loose sense). As such, lectures are quite boring and most of the information can be gathered from skimming the slides he provides. He's terribly dry but very smart, so you can't really help but respect him.

He's a great professor. The lectures are dull and sooooo long, and you'll definitely fall asleep. He really knows what he's talking about, though, and you really have no excuse for not doing well if you show up. Lots of readings, but skimming them is more than enough.
Great teacher

Mr. is a great teacher who knows his stuff. He is liberal(check fec.gov for who he's donated to) but does a great job hiding it. DO THE READINGS.the exams are multiple choice/essay. he gives the possible 6 essay questions in advance. My advice would be to draft the essays out in advance after doing readings,so that you're not doing the night B4

Amazing professor! Creates a great balance between professionalism and fun (humor) in the classroom. Material is very relevant to current affairs. He's always very accessible, and is always willing to help. He's a Prof. Emeritus, so take a class with him while he's still at the University!

Dr.  is extremely passionate about the field of Political Science and is very knowledgable about the subject matter. Yes he does tend to stray off topic, but the majority of his lectures are interesting and informative. He references the books and they are extremely helpful to study for the midterms with.

Mr.  is very knowledgeable and enthusiastic about political parties. He is a great teacher, but sometimes his lectures can be a bit dry, boring, and repetitive. The two exams he gives are 25 multiple choice questions each with a long essay response as well. He also has you do a research paper that makes up a big portion of your grade.
Professor  is incredibly well knowledge and generally a nice person. I highly recommend him.

Really great professor, one of the best I've ever had. Very friendly and communicates really well with the students. The class wasn't too challenging but wasn't easy, and I learned a lot. Highly recommended.

Awesome guy. Class is easy and he really knows his stuff. Always gives you room to voice your opinion, and grades you not on your opinion, but how you back it up and how well you know the material. Exams are straightforward and simple and he puts in a lot of cool stories and opinion pieces in his lectures. Definitely recommend him.

Prof  is a really great teacher. Helpful with anything you could ever need help with. Instant responses to emails, go out of his way for office hours etc. Lecture can be boring at times, but a lot of political anecdotes. Paper is fairly easy and exams are straight forward. Gives you essays ahead of time to study.

Great teacher. Clearly knew the topic, researched any questions he did not know the answer to. Grades very fairly, the essay was easy to get a good grade on. Attendance not required, but can be used to bump grade up if you are close. Overall great teacher, if you have the option, take him!
Professor  is a good guy. His class is easy, but you learn a lot. I thought the material was interesting - and you could see that he enjoyed teaching it.

Dean  is a good teacher. He is very informative and does a great job relating the topics to more recent elections. The class can get boring at times, but it is very interesting. The class is not too difficult and the paper topic is very interesting.
very nice and interesting! Explains everything clearly
Very nice man, interesting class; genuinely decent human being and very bright man.
Easy but boring.
No Comments
Great sense of humor.
No Comments

I enjoyed this class. He posts slides on carmen, but does add more informations during lecture. While lecture is not mandatory, I would recommend attending for the extra information. He has lots of stories that relates with the material. The test are from both lecture and books. It's not a bad class to take and has a nice curve.

I really enjoyed this class. Dr.  is a little disorganized but his lectures are interesting. His tests are from both the book and the lecture material and he loves testing on statistics. If you're interested in psychopathology you'll like the class. I recommend it.

His statistics are a lot of times way off but you need to know them for the exams anyways. You can get an A fairly easily if you read the book and attend class....but if you are really interested in Psychology- his class is frustrating because lecture doesn't relate to Adjustment at all.

Dr.  is a very nice guy who is interested in his field BUT I would caution you not to take the class. He uses outdated materials and information. If you choose to take the course make sure that you read the textbook cover to cover and write down every random statistic he says in class.

This class is not as bad as it may seem. He is a practicing psychologist so he lectures on what he thinks is interesting and then you are responsible for what is in the book for the exam. He loves statistics so pay close attention to them while your taking book notes. He also gives a pretty big curve which helps a lot. I got an A fairly easily.

The tests in this class were ridiculous, they are made up of totally random questions from the book. I found the lecture parts of the test to be quite easy, but his lectures are boring and the research is outdated. There is no new info to be learned in this class if you have already taken counseling psych and abnormal psych.

Dr.  was extremely spacey, disorganized and dull. His lectures sometimes have information that is incorrect and misleading. He relies HEAVILY on insignificant details from the book. If you read the book then that part of the test is fine, but the lecture section is ridiculous. The paper, however, was easy.

Dr.  is really nice but I would caution everyone interested in taking his Psych 681 course. First, he lectures little to nothing from the book and you are responsible for the book and lectures on the tests (they're often opposing information). He is spacey, extremely unorganized, his tests don't make sense, & has lectured incorrect information.

The class was interesting and he was a pretty good lecturer. A lot of people didn't come to class but if you go to lecture and read the book thoroughly it is easy to get an A. He doesn't cover the reading in class so you have to be motivated to do it on your own. He seemed like a really nice guy and had a lot of good stories from his clinical work.

He makes mistakes on his own exams, makes you choose between what he says in class and what the book says, and if that's not enough, you spend half the time trying to figure out what the questions are asking. Nice guy, but extremely spacey, making for an unreliable professor.

Dr.  is obviously a caring man, but he is just not the best teacher. The class was unorganized and it was hard to get questions answered. You must read the book very closely! and the topics assigned for reading will be different than that discussed in lecture. The class is so frustrating it's not worth taking even if you're highly interested.

The class is not hard if you life cold hard stats. Half of exam comes from the book (which you never go over and is indep study) and lectures that are based on date he has found on diff. subjects. He comes off anxious and is pretty scatter-brained, unprepared. His off the cuff style does not work. 3 exams and a an easy paper. Take only if needed.
This professor constantly generalizes about disorders, uses outdated research, and is super terrible at writing exams. good luck, i would not recommend him, he needs to retire

I just recently graduated from OSU and this was one of my favorite classes...and it was even in the early morning. Dr.  had some really interesting things to say and if you went to class, he gave hints for the tests. Very intelligent, educated and fair prof. Hightly recommended!
I like the guy but the test are tough.

This was my first class as a non-trad student after being out of school for 8 years. I found Dr. 's lectures interesting and relevant to the real world. He uses a lot of stories which were interesting to me. Half of the tests are from the text, so there is a lot of reading involved. If you go to class and read the text, you can get an A.

Attendence is not mandatory but I would definitely recommend going, since part of the exams come from the book. Dr.  is an amazing professor. He knows his material and is very passionate about all of it. Lectures were very interesting. I don't get up for many 9 am classes, but I hardly ever missed his!
No Comments

This is a must to take psych class!! Dr.  makes an hour and 48 min seem like half an hour. His lectures are outstanding, applicable to real world, nothing obscure. But careful!His tests have a lot of stats and are long. Even so, its a well balanced class and very informative and entertaining. Overall is great, study and you can easily get an A.

This man has no buisiness being a college proffesor.
  If a student asks a question which he doesn't know the answer to, he just guesses, often times wrongly.
  The subject matter is very easy to master, yet it is nearly impossible to get an A. This is because his tests include many random and irrelavent statistics from the text book.

Dr.  is an excellent professor. He really cares about his student's success. His course is very well-organized and he does as much as he can to make a course of this difficulty accessible to his students. The only note was some of the readings were really long, over 100 pages, and could have easily been assigned with only the abstract.

Very, very boring lectures. Stays on the same slide for an hour. Attendance does matter because you do writing assignments in each class. Very boring and drawn out talks but easy class. Tests aren't too bad as long as you study.

Overall a pretty easy class if you do the readings and attend class to complete critical thinking written assignments (1-2 paragraphs). Lectures are extremely boring. I think this class could be really interesting if taught by a different professor. If you want to attend jailprison tours, don't schedule class after this one.

Overall solid professor. Class can seem a bit slow at times and he isn't the best with powerpoint, but he certainly knows his stuff. His teaching style is ok, it's long for a 2 hour session, keeps the stats pretty interesting and clarifies whatever. Pretty approachable. Tests are easy but make sure to read because some essays answers may be ONLY found in the book but go to lecture, it's necessary to fully learn all the algorithms. Problem sets aren't bad at all, good prof, 8/10

Most boring lecturer ever. Super hard grader. Takes off points for almost no reason and then will not discuss it with the student. The class consists of 3 total grades. He doesn't respond to emails or takes forever to respond. Most of the exam answers were found in the readings that are posted. Take this if you want to hurt your GPA.

the other reviews are harsh, Dr.  is a great professor! Make sure you read the syllabus, there is an opportunity for extra credit. There are are only 2 assignments and 2 exams and also lots of opportunity for extra credit.

Hands down one of the worst professors I have ever had at this school. He looks for oddly specific answers for exams and papers and if your answers don't align exactly with what he has in mind you won't receive points. He doesn't seem to care about the fact that the majority of the class is doing poorly. Also has very few grades in the grade book.

Lazy opinion based rants with little objective fact and no dialogue.
 
 Rants include: "Why we should allow child s** dolls for pedophiles," "Why cars should be abolished," and "Why Apple is not innovative."
 
 If you want to learn anthropology, buy a textbook and form your own based opinion. I love anthropology, but this class was so disappointing.

Guy was a complete tool. Lectures felt like they went on for an eternity, full of cool little zingers that Im sure  thinks are mad clever, guaranteed to make your eyes roll so fast into your head that you'll fall out of your chair. Basically stopped showing up to class, still did fine but don't recommend if you can avoid him.

There were only 3 assignments in the course. Took the entire semester to grade 1out of the 3 assignments. Second grade was automatically generated from one of the 2 exams. This class was extremely stressful.

Worst professor I have had at this school yet and for a GENERAL EDUCATION CLASS. He is grossly ignorant and operates on his own schedule. Had covid at the beginning of the semester and had to email him 4 times before I received the content I missed. Words his questions unfairly that answers are opinion based but he does not agree with anyone.

AVOID AT ALL COSTS!!! This class had unneeded stress. He is pretentious yet ill-informed. I think they thought he was smart based on his accent but he scammed them. He made up rubrics after the fact and left little feedback that is unhelpful and seems to not make sense. He definitely skimmed them. Highest grades on the two main papers were low A's

is an incompetent wanking mess. If his unbelievable pretentiousness doesn't turn you off then the outrageous grading system and constant yawning probably will. Will not reply to emails from students despite the lack of a TA, has only remedial knowledge of the subject being taught. Overall a huge waste of time.

Grossly incompetent, what more is there to say? Takes the class way too seriously, grades off an imaginary rubric of what he likes or doesn't. Pretentious, and I had difficulty writing the way he liked even though I have been told I have been the best writer in classes before and took a writing class at the same time where I had a high A.

He seems to be nice but he is a terrible professor. The lectures are interesting, but unhelpful. He does not treat it like the throwaway, participation grade class he should treat it as. The rubrics are vague and has lengthy grading making feedback unhelpful. Grades are harsh and illogical. He doesn't know good writing. He should change or be fired

Vague grading rubric, boring and un-interactive lectures, lectures do not cover any material that is on assignments. In my case, feedback was not given until the second last week of school and did not allow the students, including I, to correct course and work off of the given feedback. This has left most students feeling helpless and withbadgrades

My main problem with this professor was that he waited until the second to last week before exams before grading one of our reading summaries, of which we had every other week since week 5, and proceed to give feedback that would have be helpful if we had another one to do. The grades on these assignments were also very harsh

The material was interesting but it would have been better if Professor  were better versed in it. He often would present information to the class that was inaccurate, sometimes multiple times a class. He also added two discussion assignments a week when classes switched to at a distance at the start of covid, which was overwhelming.

Professor  himself is a fine professor, has some charming jokes in class and is nice. My biggest complaint is that he is a fairly difficult grader and his rubrics are very vague. He will call you out in class if you're being rude and talking, but lectures do not really have much to do with your work outside of class and are interesting.
Took one of his classes thinking it would be about something I enjoy, turned out to be completely different. Would never take him again.

I'm in this class right now. Lots of complaints: The worst lecturer I've ever had. Doesn't seem like he knows the content he's trying to teach, just stands behind the computer screen and mumbles off his notes, looking down the entire time. Absolutely no class discussions. Exam was nothing he said it would be and much of it he never discussed.
I am still in this class, but this class is SO dry. He does not know what he is talking about half of the time.

DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS IF YOU CAN. There is essentially no grading criteria, and even if you follow assignment guidelines perfectly, he will find ways to lower your grade. One of the best gpa droppers out there.

I liked him a lot. While attendance is mandatory (miss more than 4 classes and you get docked a letter grade), he kept the classes very interesting and insightful. He is a very nice guy to talk to and gives good feedback on your papers. Take into account his feedback on your Op-Ed, incorporate it into your discussion paper, and you will be good.

Dr.  is an all around amazing professor. He does assign a decent amount of reading, but not more than other Sociology classes I have taken, and the readings are interesting. The lectures are super interesting and he incorporates activities into them. There was a group project, but it wasn't too difficult. Overall very helpful and caring.

He's really entertaining and a good lecturer, he keeps you engaged. My only issue is that he doesn't give a rubric for any of his exams. However, you can email him and set up office hours to go through your essay prompts and he will give good feedback. There are 3 exams, and he gives 10 prompts for each in advance. Prepare well and you'll be fine.

It's clear that Dr.  is genuinely interested in the material. And not only does he want us to learn from him, but he wants to learn from us too. It was a very comfortable and inclusive environment for intellectually stimulating conversation and I learned a lot. Had weekly 2 question quizzes, 1 group project, 1 paper, and 3 exams. Great class!

He doesn't give students feedback on exams and his rubric is based on what he thinks was important for the readings. Almost impossible to improve in this class. He talks about his favorite things about the class at the end of the semester and mentions some students by name and not others.

This class is not worth the amount of work he assigns. Every week you have to read two thirty-page academic papers and 4 or five book chapters. For exams, he gives you ten essay prompts based on these papers. you have to prepare your evidence for all of them and he'll ask for two. You basically have to write 30 essays for this class.

you will learn a lot of new things; however this class is not easy to get an A in at all. You can only loose 75 points to still get an A-. All exams are essays with no rubric or guidlines. There are ALOT of reading and weekly quizzes about these readings. I have friends who took this class with a different prof and said it was way easier.

Professor  is very passionate about the material and it shows in his lectures. Very interesting content but should attend class if you want to do well on the exams. If you take good notes, preparing for the essay exams is easy. There is a fair amount of outside work to do for this class but it was all interesting and informative.

This class is not an easy A for a gen ed. He is a harsh grader, but only because he wants you to learn. Content is interesting, but there is a ton of outside work. Go to class because there are pop quizzes that are 20% if your grade on the homework readings. You have to try hard in this class to do well and one grade can offset your entire grade

If you have the option to take a different GE or 1101H with a different professor take it! The exams are only essays and he gives you the prompts ahead of time. He is a very very harsh grader. There is no rubric and hes okay with giving a large amount of the class Cs and Ds. Dont take this class if youre expecting an easy A.

Dr.  is an amazing professor and extremely caring! The only bad part of his class was the harsh attendance policy - no makeups, even if you were sick and have a doctor's note. He was a thoroughly engaging professor with a strong passion for sociology.

Took this class to fulfill an honors GE. Requires A LOT of outside reading, & exams are in class essays. A little disappointed that I received a B in this class (was looking for an easy GPA booster) but did not regret the time I spent in the class. He's really passionate about the topics and cares for his students! Learned a lot.

Dr.  is a great professor who makes the subject very interesting both through what he talks about in class and the setup of the course. Lots of interaction with peers. You have to go to class everyday and do the readings, which are a lot, but the class itself is not too hard.

Dr.  is awesome. He is passionate about the material and his student's success. He makes a real effort to get to know everyone in the class and to offer constructive feedback. The class requires a lot of reading, but it is specific books that  picks out, all of which are pretty interesting. I really enjoyed this class and learned a ton.

is THE MAN. One of my favorite professors here at Ohio State. Truly cares about his students and made the subject super interesting. Tests are challenging but he gives you the essay prompts before the exam.

Dr.  was one of the best professors I've had at Ohio State. His lectures really made me care about sociological topics and changed my worldview. His tests are pretty tough, but if you take the time to prepare for them (and meet with him to review your preparation), you'll get an A. Buy or rent the books, as the test is based on them.

While learning the content was interesting, when it came to the exams he was a tough grader. He gives you ten possible topics for essays relevant to the recent material, and then chooses two for you to write essays on for the exam. He really expects you to make them quality essays, so it wasn't as easy as I expected.

He was a fantastic teacher and really made me learn to love sociology! There is a good deal of reading in the class, and pop quizzes, but the pop quizzes are always just "give me the main theme or summary" so they aren't too specific. Overall, Dr.  is a great guy, and also a hilarious lecturer. He made going to class worth it.

Professor  was one of my favorite professors that I have ever had. He is very entertaining, and makes the topic more interesting than it actually is. He is a fair grader, but you do definitely have to work for a good grade. He is not intimidating and always there to help. Definitely take his class if you get a chance!

Favorite college class. He really knows his stuff & is super passionate. He presents the information in an interesting way that makes you want to pay attention. There is a lot of group work & you actually get to know the people in the class which made it more fun. Just do the reading & pay attention. Exams aren't bad if you put in the effort

Dr.  is one of my favorite instructors of all the teachers I have ever had. He's a character and says something that makes the entire class laugh every 5 minutes. Truly enjoyed his class. He assigns really long reading assignments for homework that can be pretty unbearable but you have to do them to pass quizzes and exams. Take his class.

There's a decent amount of reading but it's not too hard. Many classes will have a quick writing assignment (3-4 sentence reaction to a concept) that is your "attendance" grade. I don't get how she's a 2.7, I showed up about 50% of the time and got a B. Her tests are scantron and not that hard if you pay attention and read.

She takes random attendance - so go to every class. She talks really fast & studdars so I recommend you record her lectures. Her lectures are 90% graphs that will be translated to 50 or 100 question multiple choice. No curve and only 4 assignments (2 exams & 2 papers) for the whole semester.
Great professor. Really loves to teach. Loved the class. Grades the papers harshly and you definitely have to study for exams because there's a lot of content. Overall though, enjoyed the class.

She is a very enthusiastic and supportive. Lectures can get very boring very quickly, but that tends to be the nature of college classes. She does talk pretty fast, but will ask to make sure you understood the material. One midterm and final (study guides given), group project and participation. Do the work and studying and get the grade you want.

Professor  is a thoroughly outstanding instructor who took a real interest in my success. She strikes a careful balance between imparting information and allowing free discussion. If I could repeat this class every quarter, I would (and I'd bet I'd learn something new every time!) I cannot speak highly enough of the overall experience.
She is incredibly frustrating to listen to - she tends to stutter and ramble a lot. Ridiculous amount of reading assigned, and her grading is tough despite unclear expectations. Not recommended.

Honestly, I have nothing but positive things to say about this teacher. She was very friendly and approachable. The class was generally interesting and her expectations were clear most of the time. She allowed me to move my final time to a more convenient time, which I greatly appreciated. I would definitely recommend taking her course.
She was hard to follow...maybe needs to update her technology use in class. She doesn't like to give A's on her papers.

EXCELLENT PROF! She is SO smart! Talks very quickly, and is easy to zone out so bring a snack or soda to class. Go to class every day and take detailed notes (try to write everything she says) and you will do okay. Promptly responds to emails and is understanding of personal problems that conflict with class. Highly recommended(esp 4 soc majors)!

I took this as a GEC course and while she is helpful, responds quickly to emails, and is enthusiastic and funny, she graded hard, took bad notes on the board, and got off track and confusing sometimes during lecture. I worked really hard for a poor grade, so I'd advise taking this with another professor or a finding a different GEC.

The discussions we had were very interesting for the most part-- takes input from a lot of people which is important. A lot of the readings are DRY, and sometimes she grades as if we were sociology majors (I don't think think one of us was). Sometimes she made the material really interesting, and sometimes I couldn't help but bring sudoku.
Extremely helpful and kept the class entertaining.

This professor was very enthusiastic, she was willing to help and very easy to talk to. She doesn't make it mandatory to come to class but if you do majority of what's on the exams is talked about. The first exam was very easy but the final was kind basically to get the slackers.....
I was really inspired by her! She makes things really interesting and she's really easy to talk to! I want to look into the social stratification minor, that's how interesting she made the class!

This class was my favorite class ever at OSU (and I am a science major!) and she was probably the best prof I have ever had either. 2-5 pg essays,2 exams, and participation determine your grade. Fair grader...more than willing to help on essays. I didnt think tests were hard if you had good notes and of course studied! AMAZING! Take her class!

Wonderful lecturer, keeps things interesting and fun, and loves to have debates/conversations among the class. She is a very fair grader, but don't expect to be able to slack off. Just pay attention in class, read the book, and do your work, and you'll be fine. Highly recommended.

Very interesting lecturer. Kept most students interest. Made subject matter interesting and easy to understand. Creates her own exams so they went along with what was learned in lecture. I had two 5 page papers to do for the class but they were nothing super difficult.

This was a really hard class, but she is a fair grader and very intelligent. You can tell how passionate she is about the subject matter just by how involved she gets into her talks in class. Her lectures are really concise and, at times, even stunning. I hate sociology but I would take another class with her anyday.

love love love this prof. her lectures are interesting and she knows with extreme detail what she is talking about. she makes classes interesting by addressing relevant issues. always willing to go out of her way to help students if they need it. take her! friends had her for h101 and they liked her too!

She's a great teacher, and she made H101 extremely fun, interesting & relateable. She's a bit of a tough grader, but it's nothing unreasonable. I agree though, if you take H101, take it with her. And make sure you speak up. She likes people who talk a lot.

Mr.  is one of the best professors I have had! This class is really an easy A if you try. Sometimes his grading is a little tough but he gives you PLENTY of opportunities to make up for any points you might have lost. He will literally give you the answer if you meet with him and he's a great guy in general who really wants you to pass.

Wow where do I start, took an online race in America class, the work is absolutely ridiculous for it being a 3000 level class. Its way tooo much reading he nitpicks everything on each of your assignments, if you dont add a word count on your assignments which are 6 total due every Wednesday and Friday you will lose all points. RUN RUN RUN AWAY

It was a pretty standard sociology class. He did a good job and really tried to get the class to debate the readings. (He did a pretty good job considering our class was at 8:00am). I wasn't all that interested in the class because it was just a gen ed, but other classmates got more into it. He has a very strict no phone/technology policy.

You get as much out of this class as you get in. Most of the in-class lectures are discussions, and  loves letting the students share their opinions on the topics being discussed in class. He's always available for his office hours, and will talk to you even if you don't have any specific questions.

This class is an actual joke in terms of difficulty.  himself isn't a native English speaker so he pretty much gives everyone 100% on all assignments as long as they are turned in. While his lectures are fairly interesting and intuitive, the homework for this class is high school level. Enroll in this class for an easy break.

While  is a very nice man and a great professor to just talk to, his class really didn't add anything to my academic experience. He never really had a clear lesson plan and the purpose of the whole course seemed to just be one big workshop for the final paper. Basically everything was graded for completeness, an easy A, but a fun class

He can be pretty crass when leaving feedback on your assignments, especially essays. In my opinion, he lets his leftist bias show while teaching the class. For example, he asked us to asses where racial tension was in the U.S, but when he graded it he acted like there was only one right answer. There are many other examples of his leftist bias.
Engaging, informative lectures. Reading material, while often lengthy, is interesting. Requires a lot of writing. Overall excellent professor and I learned a lot from him.

Class had zero quizzes or tests. Had a reading with summary and opinion article due every week and two essays.  seems to be very smart and wants everyone to succeed. Class got boring at times but he recognizes that we have many more difficult classes.

This was a great class! You watch documentaries that cover many social issues that are very interesting. His accent did frighten me at first because I have had difficulty understanding him during the first two lectures but I grew used to it and he uses his experiences coming from a Latin American family which helps relay the material.

I took his online class and its the easiest A I've had so far at OSU. There was a lot of work, but he was a super lenient grader. The material was also really interesting. I would definitely take him again!

This class was an easy A. There were weekly assignments (about 4-7 per week) and 2 essays. No tests. Just had to answer 1 review question and a summary on an article for homework and write in the discussion board w/ other students. It's some work but didn't take up all my summer time.

Real nice guy but theres a good amount of work in the class. Super easy grader though, I've gotten 100% on the weekly homework. He's very flexible and really listens to students about the assignments. He lets you turn things in late, and there's a ton of extra credit opportunities. Nice guy.

Thought provoking and stimulating. Spoke w/ him outside of class & corresponded with him over email several times. Prof.  requires alot of work on behalf of the student. If you assume equal responsibility for your education, everything you need to learn is provided. If you prefer, as many do, to be told precisely what to think, stay away.

Disorganized, making it very hard to track your performance. Non-communicative, making it a giant pain to resolve any issues. Prompts and instructions were contridictory. The subject matter was interesting, but he was so clearly dismissive about actually helping us that we all had to start an email group just to decipher the assignment prompts.

Great Professor. He genuinely cares about the class and the topics. You just have to read some online articles and write a page summary, one movie group project, and the 2 midterms (which were not hard). You can miss 4 classes but if you know you will miss more it will drop you 10% from your final grade automatically.

You'll be doing a lot of reading for the class, but the articles are pretty interesting. Presentations in class and discussions are interesting but can get pretty heated if a few people start arguing. He always wants to hear your opinion, which is pretty cool.

English is not his first language; has an accent but you get used to it. good teacher. Youll read a lot (20 page essays per week andthen write summary). Attendance is basically mandatory although you are allowed to miss a few classes. Tests are easy essays. This class was one of my favorites. learned a lot. Heated debates! never used the textbook

I think he genuinely wants his students to learn the material, but his lectures were confusing. Even though he is a non-native speaker, I feel like the language barrier was not the issue. He just had a really hard time teaching the material due to being very disorganized. We wrote lots of papers, and I don't think he really graded any of them.

Chip is a cool dude, but his class is BORING. The class is mostly a discussion on readings and you must participate. There is no final which is nice but there is a quiz due before every class, and it's heavily based on the readings. And you only get 5 minutes on the quiz. Don't be surprised if you end up falling asleep during his lectures.

Chip is really kind, but he cares more about content then students. There is a quiz before every class and the Assignments take forever. If you are just taking this class to get an easy A, its not. you will work for it. The class was very thought provoking though.

Chip is a great professor, he makes the classroom a conversation more than just a lecture hall. The material he covers is great and really has you think about the world of media and communication. I learned a lot from him. Tests and assignments are a little hard but if you put in the time you will do well.

Chip is simply one of the best professors I had at OSU but his class is not for everyone. There is a lot of reading and technology use is frowned upon. But if you are interested in communication or politics, this is a must-take. A course that will truly change your worldview if you put in the effort. Don't skip class (random attendance sign-ups).

Had Chip for Political Comm, never had him for a pre-req course. I loved his class though. Interesting, intense material. People think he's tough, but guess what: he treats his students like adults and wants to make class a discussion, not a lecture. Considerable reading and discussion to expect, but absolutely a get out what you put in course.

Do not take his classes. The class material could be incredibly easy to understand, and he tries to make it sound more complicated to suit his ego. His tests are unnecessarily difficult and I feel like he does it on purpose. He doesn't get enough love from his department so he takes it out on the students. Stay away from him.

"Chip" may be the worst professor at Ohio State. He is so condescending and full of himself and made the class harder and more boring than it ever needed to be. I looked up his rating before I took the class and he seemed okay but trust me he is not. I hated every second I spent in this class and was beyond glad to see the last of him.
He is funny!

"Chip" is resentful his research can't earn grants and takes it out on students by taking a entry level class full of athletes and people who are just trying to get into the major way to seriously. He makes things unnecessarily difficult and believes he is the "cool" teacher but is unhelpful and screws students over on exams and quizzes. Avoid him!

Chip is great. He really understands theory, but his has a background political communications and often uses political examples for class. This could be helpful in a class with 600 students because everyone has a basic knowledge on political issues. He DOES NOT post lectures note online, so read the textbook & going to office hours &/or see a TA.

Chip is a really nice guy and knows how to explain the material and give good examples. He doesn't give out extra credit and there are only 3 exams, 10 quizzes and 5 CREP experiment points but the material is common sense and easy to grasp. He also gives you a chance to take everything a second time and get the average of your scores.
he took this class waaaay too seriously for a 100 level Comm class. offers no extra credit and averages your exams and quizzes instead of taking your better score

there is NO opportunity for extra credit and the exam questions can be a little tricky. Make sure you read the questions in entirety. Chip is a good guy but You must come to class to get notes because he wont give them out for any reason. Make a friend in his class so you can give notes to each other. You have to have the book to pass quizzes.
Relatively easy. Need to attend class for notes. Need textbook for quizzes. Exams are somewhat harder than they need to be, but not impossible.

The questions on the exams are right from the power point notes. If you go to class or get the notes from someone it's an easy class. You also are allowed to take exams twice and average the scores. Overall he made the class interesting and I would take him again.

"Chip" is pessimistic and not helpful when it comes to students individually. Lecture notes are ridiculous (grammar, length) and he doesn't have the ability to clarify. He puts most of his work on his TA's and will ramble during lecture- hard to focus. The class is too large for him to care.CERTAINLY made this course more difficult than needed

He was a nice guy who explained the concepts really well and made the subject interesting. His exams were straight forward from the material and were not trying to trick or mislead, just test your knowledge

At first the class seems difficult but after the first text it's very predictable. The quizzes and exams are straight out of the textbook and notes. Make sure you go to class because he doesn't post his notes. Overall the class really isn't too bad.

He's really funny and makes lectures pretty interesting and fun which made me look forward to going to class. Very interactive with the students during class and clarifies the material better than the textbook does. The book is necessary for both the exams and online quizzes.

He makes class pretty interesting. You don't need to attend because basically the same stuff is in the text book, but he makes it so easy to understand. He's very organized so taking notes is easy. Tests are simple as long as you reread notes and text.

This is actually the most interesting class I have taken in OSU. If you are really into social psych, you would like this class. There's no assignments, so final grade is only dependent on exams, which are hard but the grade is curved according to the ranking. Attendance is not mandatory but super helpful if you want to get a good grade.

This was the most boring class I have even taken at Ohio State. If you are a psychology major I recommend taking ANY other class as your upper level class. Theres only 3 exams that count towards your grade and thats it. It wasn't too hard just honestly SO SO SO boring

I agree that class average was a D on every test, but a curve makes it a B-. All you need to do to do well is show up to class and take notes on the research he discusses. He is a great, knowledgable professor. He even admitted he makes the tests hard because it's an advanced class, but he curves greatly. don't blame a poff because you don't study!
Good luck passing this class. Averages on the exams are D's. Hardest class I've ever taken and he makes his tests unpassable. Do not take this course!!!

I literally switched my major to public health after this class. I would say that the time in class is not productive, and most of the homework out of class takes some time to do (1 page writing and 1 easy quiz a week for the most part), but the content is very interesting. We read novels relating to public health. Loved this class and professor
Not difficult but not particularly interesting. Seems generally nice but came off as very condescending in emails and one-ones.
A nice enough professor, but not very engaging and often comes across as condescending

Class consisted of asynchronously watching a lecture and videos each week and then 1 page reflections about what you watch. In person meetings were a lot of cool guest lecturers and discussions about topics. Not very much work, no tests. 1 group research paper and 1 "final" project that is really easy

I took case studies in epidemiology my freshman year and loved having Dr. . Even though the class was 3 hours long and in the evenings, I always looked forward to it. She gave group projects, but they were interesting and actually helped us learn the material. She also brought snacks every week.

I heard amazing things about this class, but with the way it is set up I was super disappointed. A different TA teaches each module and each quiz is written completely differently making them hard to study for. Her rubrics and syllabus are extremely vague on projects as well, and asking for clarity from her or the TAs was not helpful at all.

The best class I've taken at Ohio State so far. Small class, about 15 people and totally focused on case studies. For older students, great way to apply what you've learned in other classes. For freshmen, great opportunity to learn from her and students that have been in the program
She is an alright professor. Studying is an absolute in her class. Material is easy. Most tests are all multiple choice.

I have taken a few classes with . She's a very good teacher and has lots of ways to make lecture not so boring. Her tests are tough though. You really need to study and understand what's going on. Her classes are interesting but can be tough. It's really not a slack-off kind of class.
Dr.  is one of the best profs I've ever had! I'm in my senior year and her classes are great.
I hated her class. Very boring, and she failed me by .5 points and would not do anything about. She makes people do expeirments that dont count for anything. This class was just plain stupid to take.
She is the reason I want to study Psychology!.....A wonderful & very talented prof. Her test are not easy ....but you will learn a lot. I enjoy all her classes!.......
I had a couple of classes with Dr. . She was amazing in all of them. She changed the direction of my entire college experience. She was great in all ways.

She is an excellent professor and her class was really a lot of fun. She is very helpful at making sure everyone understands, and throws in plenty of interesting stories, examples and analogies. I would definitely recommend her to anyone!

Dr.   was one of the most passionate and amazing professors I had ever had. She made me discover a love for a topic I never thought was possible, demography. She encourages students to have open discussions and is ok with going off track if it means have a good in depth conversation. She is truly an amazing soul and an awesome professor!

I loved Dr. ! She removed a lot of material that gave students trouble in the past and constantly went at a pace she felt the class was understanding. Very straightforward of what is required and a fairly easy class if you just show up and pay attention.

Dr. 's lectures were extremely long, but since it was only once a week it isn't too bad. She is always considerate of whether or not students understand the subject. The class is simple for a statistics class, and is easy if you can comprehend the material. She gives tons of extra credit, and it's composed of 4 assignments and 2 exams

She seems to be better than the reviews before me. She really seems to try hard to explain things & she is helpful if you ask questions. The lectures are really long and boring though. There's 4 HW assignments that aren't too bad and a midterm and final. She also takes attendance and gives extra credit every class. All the grades were graded fast.

Extremely boring. The information is easy to grasp, but she makes it more complicated than it needs to be. I'd highly recommend if you have to take this class, take it with a different professor. this class was SO easy! gives extra credit in every lecture, and attendance is mandatory. she makes the material very clear and gives many examples. i thought stats would be my hardest class but ended up with an A very easily. 4 assignments and 2 exams. i think our class had 18 extra credit points given over the quarter. take her!
She made everything pretty clear. Especially when learning stats it is easy to be confused, but she explains it very well and has many examples which helps!

Whoever says she is bad is wrong. Dr  is a really good teacher and her class is easy unless you are an idiot. She explains everything very well in class and anything you dont understand can be found in the book or you can ask and she's very helpful.
Very easy on the eyes
No one ever knew what she was talking about. When questions were asked, she only repeated herself and did not give us a good explanation
A little unorganized at times, but overall not a bad professor. If anything, the TA's will prevent you from understanding the material by making things more confusing than necessary.

Dr.  was young, and it showed. Psych of stereotyping and prejudice is an incredibly interesting class and Dr.  is a great professor. I highly recommend this class. Horrible professor. Teaches with powerpoint and goes WAY too fast to write anything down so make sure you print off the notes.So, if you learn better by writing things down you're screwed. This guy went to Harvard and has a great teaching ethic! He is very clear and precise in what he will test on, as long as you read the book and study his notes! Probably one of my favorite professors yet! I suggest going to class everyday in order to get a good grade in the course! I came out with a B!

Very dedicated to his subject matter. You can tell that Dr.  lives, breathes and eats social psychology. The class is by no means a walk in the park, but if you read the book in tandem with lectures, you'll do fine. On a side note, he indirectly inspired me to pursue a career in education and research.

Professor  is a good teacher. He is very clear when presenting the material and is funny at times. He was also very helpful to those who were having a hard time with the material. There are two papers, which were pretty easy, and three exams which were very difficult. 50% of the exam is from the book while 50% is from the lectures. His exams

Dr  is fairly smart and humorous. To be honest, the exams are hard compared to other psych exams that I have taken. The lecture is fun but the textbook is so boring! Psychology of prejudice and discrimination is the least psych class that u should choose.

He is clear in telling students what he expects from them. His exams can be moderately hard if you expect that memorizing things will get you off with a good grade (don?t write note cards prior to exams). Study the concepts from the book and make sure that you revise his lecture notes.

Papers were easy to write. Reading is boring, but do it. The tests are impossible because it is filled with so many tricks and lures. Dr.  knows his stuff and makes it very easy to learn all of the material. His tests are tough, but not impossible. There are TONS of theories to learn and lots of reading to do in order to pass.

Very interesting class. He's a great teacher. The book is necessary. It is not a hard read, just dry. But you must read to get a good grade for this class. Tests are 50% lecture/ 50% book. Two papers, but easy to write. I would suggest this teacher for this class. He is easy to understand and willing to answer any questions. Quick to e-mail back.

I took this class in sp 08. Don't know what the big deal is why people are saying it was hard. You have to read the book!!!! Do what ur suppose to do and ull get an A!
This class is hard. It's a lot of work. But if you're getting a B.S. you have to take a class like this to graduate, and I suggest taking this one because social psych is interesting.

Going to class helps out a lot and a lot of questions are from the textbook and not discussed in class. He is very clear in lecture on what he expects. On the two short essays, follow EXACTLY. If you deviate or try to go "above and beyond" he will FAIL YOU!
DO NOT take his class

Psychology is my major and this class made me question whether or not I wanted to do it. He made the tests way too difficult and gave us a curve because most of the class did poorly. The only reason I passed was because of the good curve!
He was great. Exams were difficult, but there was a nice curve. I thoroughly enjoyed his class, and hope to take 520 with him as well.
sucks. get another professor if you can. his tests are way too hard. it's like he enjoys watching you suffer through the exams. don't say i didn't warn you.

he talks way too fast and he likes to make his tests ridiculously hard.. like to the point where it's just unnecessary. Dr.  is not patient or inviting when it comes to students questions. She responds in quite a defensive and irritated manner. She is also very contradictory. She says she is not trying to trick you and writes her tests/assignments in a very technical way.

She is a tough grader, but she intends well. She wants to make sure youâ€™re prepared and that you know your material. The book for the class is arduous, but her lectures really help concepts come to life and the homeworks help make those concepts more concrete. I would highly recommend her!

Great professor! Really cares about students. Easy grader, if you think something was misgraded you can ask to change it.
 
 Not many assignments and they are easy and you'll learn. Few small assignments for participation, 2 exams (easy), 1 final paper that is broken up throughout semester. Plus he brings his dog!
Dr. is very passionate about what he teaches and it definitely shows. He is willing to answer questions and help students succeed. He explains everything in detail and keep us entertained.

Lectures are sometimes boring but if you pay attention and take notes in lecture you'll do well on the exams. Reading quizzes are not hard because he goes over reading materials during lecture so even if you don't actually read you'll still get full points on the quizzes.

Pretty easy class while still learning a lot.  is a really good story teller so his lectures are pretty interesting. The review sessions before the midterm and final covered everything and the paper is broken down so its not very hard.

Attendance counts as extra credit & he brings a dog. Lectures are extremely boring. Second half of class after the midterm is more interesting. Paper is broken into parts so no stress to put all together. Exams are easy, he gives you a study guide & just know what he says. Hard to reach out of class. Quizzes are easy. Boring, but easy A.
Professor  is great! Nicest dude, really knows his stuff, very good lecturer. Hard to get a hold of sometimes, though.

I showed up to class 5 times the whole semester; the midterm, to turn in the different parts of the paper, and the final. You don't need to show up. Don't know how its possible but he never actually taught. He talked about what he was going to talk about for 90 minutes! must read the textbook in order to fill out the study guides. shouldn't be teaching an intro neuroscience class. Seems like his lectures are aimed more towards grad students. 3 exams are worth almost all of your grade and require an insane amount of studying. 2 midterms, 1 final, 1 group presentation, 1 unofficial presentation and 1 short essay. The grading is clear. No text book use. Not too difficult but not too easy. 3 hr long lecture was boring but overall not bad. Never touched textbook...

Easy, lecture wasn't necessary as he basically read right off slides, but exams are online and you have ample time

He was an Amazing teacher; very informative and the class was a breeze (very easy)

Very boring lectures. I found myself learning more from the textbook than the lectures. Tests were moderate.. not impossible though.

Super nice guy, crazy-making quiet/scattered lecturer. If you don't know much about neuroscience you'll have to teach yourself from the book (what I did) or spend lots of time with him one-on-one. He's probably much better for advanced students.

The most boring class of my existence. Make sure you peep her extra credit point, as it would've allowed for me to not take the final haha. A fantastic lecturer. I now go out of my way to find what class he teaches so that I can schedule it. My favorite professor at OSU.

Very easy going and very understanding. Very enthusiastic about psychology and really engages the audience. I took his online class and he posted videos of all his lectures and the powerpoints he used. He could not have been more clear of what was expected from the students.
